BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:March Member Hour: 75th Anniversary and New Visions for the Perman
 ent Collection
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260313T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260313T100000
UID:10001954-1773392400-1773396000@www.taubmanmuseum.org
DESCRIPTION:Nancy Lorenz: The Elements			\n		\n	\n\n\n\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n		
 		\n									\n				\n				\n								\n					Jerome Myers (United States\, 18
 67–1940)\, Evening Glow (detail)\, 1904\, oil on board\, Taubman Museum 
 of Art\, Gift of Cynthia and Heywood Fralin in Honor of the Museum’s 75t
 h Anniversary\, 2025.007				\n							\n		\n	\n\n\n\n	\n		\n			\n\n	\n		\n\
 nJoin Laura K. Higgins\, Curator of 75th Anniversary Gifts to the Permanen
 t Collection\, for guided spotlights in the Museum’s newest exhibition\,
  75th Anniversary: New Visions for the Permanent Collection. \n\n\n\nFor 7
 5 years\, the Museum’s Permanent Collection has been shaped by landmark 
 gifts\, sustained generosity\, and careful stewardship. What began as a re
 gional commitment to art has grown into a collection defined by depth\, co
 ntinuity\, and evolving perspective. \n\n\n\nThis exhibition reflects both
  history and momentum. At its core are gifts made in honor of the Museum
 ’s 75th Anniversary — works that expand the Collection across media\, 
 cultures\, and time periods. Installed in dialogue with longstanding holdi
 ngs\, these new acquisitions illuminate established strengths while openin
 g new areas of inquiry. \n\n\n\nThroughout the galleries\, historical foun
 dations and contemporary voices are interwoven. Photography speaks across 
 generations\; regional narratives sit alongside global traditions\; establ
 ished icons are reframed through present-day perspectives. \n\n\n\nA perma
 nent collection is not static. It is built over time\, shaped by community
  support\, guided by professional standards\, and entrusted to future gene
 rations. With these 152 gifts\, this anniversary marks both a milestone an
 d a beginning — honoring the past while setting the course for what come
 s next. \n\n\n\nMembers are encouraged to bring up to two paying guests fo
 r this special morning program.  \n\n\n\nMembers: Free | Member Guests: $1
 0 \n\n	\n\n\n\n	\n				\n			\n				\n			\n			\n				Add to Calendar\n								
 \n			\n		\n				\n			\n				\n					\n				\n			\n			\n				Driving? Get Direct
 ions\n			\n		\n		\n			\n				\n			\n			\n				Share  This!\n			\n		\n						\
 n			\n				\n			\n			\n				Register Now\n			\n		\n			\n	\n				\n			Exhibiti
 on and educational programming support for 75th Anniversary: New Visions f
 or the Collection are supported in part by the Richard & Caroline T. Gwath
 mey Memorial Trust\, Bank of America\, N.A.\, Trustee. \n		\n				\n		\n			
 			\n				\n					\n						Date:					 \n					\n						\n							\n								\n			
 						Feb 04\, 2027								\n								\n																											\n						
 					May 16\, 2027\n\nSource: https://www.taubmanmuseum.org/march-member-h
 our-75th-anniversary
LOCATION:Taubman Museum of Art\, 110 Salem Ave SE\, Roanoke\, VA\, 24011\,
  United States
URL:https://www.taubmanmuseum.org/march-member-hour-75th-anniversary
