 		\n									\n				\n				\n								\n					LeUyen Pham (Vietnamese-American
 \, born 1973)\, The Princess in Black and the Giant Problem\, 2020. Waterc
 olor and ink on paper © 2020 LeUyen Pham				\n							\n		\n	\n\n\n\n	\n		
 \n			\n\n	\n		\n\nLet’s celebrate Spring Break with a fun morning creati
 ng art!  \n\n\n\nThe theme of this one-day mini-camp will be centered arou
 nd books.  \n\n\n\nInspired by our latest exhibition\, LeUyen Came Along: 
 The Art of LeUyen Pham\, participants will learn about the illustrative ar
 t and books that LeUyen has created in her long career. \n\n\n\nSome class
 ics you may recognize include “Vampirina Ballerina\,” “The Princess 
 in Black\,” and “Itty-Bitty Kitty-Corn\,” and more! \n\n\n\nChildren
  will get to create everything from a bookmark and collage to their very o
 wn book. \n\n\n\nThis camp is for children kindergarten through fifth grad
 e. \n\n\n\nRegistration required. \n\n\n\nMembers: $60 | General Public: $
 75 \n\n\n\nNot a member? Join today for discounts on camps and classes\, e
 xclusive invites\, free reciprocal admission to the Virginia Museum of Fin
 e Arts in Richmond\, and more. Click here to learn more and become a membe
 r.  \n\n\n\nAlong Came LeUyen: The Art of LeUyen Pham was organized by the
  National Center for Children’s Illustrated Literature\, Abilene\, Texas
 . \n\n	\n\n\n\n	\n				\n			\n				\n			\n			\n				Add to Calendar\n								
